												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/pamelanewton/">Pamela Newton</a></h6>
													Pamela <span class="il">Newton</span> has written essays and cultural criticism for publications including <i>Time Out New York, The New York Times Magazine, O the Oprah Magazine, American Theatre, National Book Review, The Huffington Post</i>, and others. She also wrote one of the monologues in Nora and Delia Ephron’s play, <i>Love, Loss, and What I Wore</i>. She teaches writing in the English department at Yale University.																									</div>
